So one day, I came up with the idea to make bread at home. Now I can eat roti by myself and my husband prepares it for me. It’s super simple and delicious. I hope girls and women in Laos will enjoy this recipe. I would love to invite them to my bakery one day when I opened. Stay home girls and take care of yourself much especially younger girls, they just love boys too much that forget everything, toys, bikes, arms, sweets, biscuits, watches. When they grow old, they will be alone and poor.

Secret Recipe: Lentil flatbread

Ingredients

Boiled lentils (1/2 cup)

1 onion

1 garlic cloves

1 cup of flour

1/2 teaspoon of turmeric powder

1 teaspoon of salt

1 teaspoon of vegetable oil (you can use avocado oil or olive oil)

.

Directions

Preheat oven at 350F.

Place the lentils and the vegetables at a blender. Blitz them until it has a smooth and creamy thickness. If necessary add some water to get the right texture. I just use some olive oil or avocado oil so get the right texture.

Place the mix in a bowl and add the flour, salt and turmeric powder. Knead the bread
